This paper deals with wireless networks and reinforcement learning, which are both topics that fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of Multi-Armed Bandits (MABs) and exploration-exploitation trade-off are also common in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of decentralized mechanisms, which can be related to Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on achieving optimal proportional fairness, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
